### Day 17 - HubSpot-style API Error Handling Pattern
# This file is documentation/evidence only. Do not commit real tokens.
# Use with VS Code REST Client or similar tools.
# Requires environment variable:
# HUBSPOT_PRIVATE_APP_TOKEN=pat-na1-...

@baseUrl = https://api.hubapi.com
@token = {{$dotenv HUBSPOT_PRIVATE_APP_TOKEN}}

### Auth/read sanity check
GET {{baseUrl}}/crm/v3/objects/contacts?limit=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Example search request that should be wrapped in error handling
POST {{baseUrl}}/crm/v3/objects/contacts/search
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "filterGroups": [
    {
      "filters": [
        {
          "propertyName": "email",
          "operator": "EQ",
          "value": "sarah.jones@meridianrail.co.uk"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "properties": ["email", "firstname", "lastname", "lifecyclestage"],
  "limit": 1
}

### Error handling notes
# 400 -> validation / payload review
# 401/403 -> token or private app scope review
# 409 -> conflict / dedupe review
# 429 -> retry after backoff / rate-limit handling
# 5xx -> transient API failure / retry with max attempts
